s book contains the full text of Terán's diary—which has never before been published—edited and annotated by Jack Jackson and translated into English by John Wheat. The introduction and epilogue place the diary in historical context, revealing the significant role that Terán played in setting Mexican policy for Texas between 1828 and 1832.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aGeneralszMexicovDiaries. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh1 aCheatham, Scooter.1 aJackson, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Jack, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMarshall, Lynn.1 aWheat, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWheat, John.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292799004423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292799004/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK